lchat - line chat frontend

lchat (line chat) is a line oriented front end for ii-like chat
programs. It handles input from keyboard and output file in parallel,
allowing you to type messages while new chat lines are arriving.
Its main focus is on usability and simplicity.

lchat can be used as frontend for the following programs and protocols:
  - ii    for IRC
  - ratox for Tox
  - sj/jj for XMPP
  - icb   for ICB
